<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007</DATELINE><TITLE>Not so fast: adaptive suppression of innate immunity</TITLE><BODY>The innate and adaptive immune systems act in concert to effectively combat infection while minimizing collater al damage caused by the host immune response. T cells of the adaptive immune system have now been shown to suppress overzealous early innate responses to infection that can lead to 'cytokine storm'–mediated death (pages 1248–1252).&#3;</BODY></TEXT>